Ligue 1 club, OGC Nice have submitted a new tempting offer for Lorient forward, Terem Moffi. Nice had made several attempts to sign the Nigeria international but had their overtures turned down by Lorient. Moffi, according to reports has already agreed on personal terms with Nice. Olympic Marseille and West Ham United were interested in the player but he reportedly turned the two clubs down after they agreed on a deal with Lorient. Nice’s current offer is €30m including bonuses, something that the Lorient management wanted. Moffi has scored 12 goals in 20 league appearances for Les Merlus this season.